0 Source: WRO-2026-RM-Elementary-BI-All.pdf, steps 101-112 (cables build).
0 Per-step part counts (counts × 2 for the pair built in parallel):
0   Step 101: 4× 2x4 yellow brick                  → 2 per cable
0   Step 102: 2× 2x4 white brick                   → 1 per cable
0   Step 103: 2× 1x6 black technic brick (3894)    → 1 per cable
0   Step 104: 4× 1x6 white brick                   → 2 per cable
0   Step 105: 2× 2x2 black brick                   → 1 per cable
0   Step 106: 4× 2x2 white brick                   → 2 per cable
0   Step 107: 2× 2x4 yellow brick                  → 1 per cable
0   Step 108: 4× 2x4 yellow brick                  → 2 per cable
0   Step 109: 4× 1x6 white brick                   → 2 per cable
0   Step 110: 2× 1x2 brick with pin + 2× 2x4 white → 1+1 per cable
0   Step 111: 2× 1x2 brick with pin + 2× 2x4 white → 1+1 per cable
0 Total: ~14 bricks per cable; world.xml instantiates 2 of these.
